<figureCitation id="132A69F6647DFFE28BAE48CEFECB12A3" box="[151,302,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–27" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,192,1838]" captionTargetId="figure-21@14.[151,1436,181,1849]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 21–27. Pericoma estrelica spec. nov.: 21 terminalia ventral view; 22 wing. Heteroberdeniella jaramensis: 23 styles, aedeagus and hypandrium; 24 aedeagus. H. guadarramica sp. nov.: 25 wing; 26 styles, aedeagus, and hypandrium; 27 epandrium with appendages and hypoproct. Scale bars: Figs 22, 25—1 mm; figs 21, 23, 24, 26, 27—0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6488102" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6488102/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="50">Figure 21–22</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAE7573647DFFE28BAE4976FC391337" blockId="13.[151,1437,259,970]" pageId="13" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B965A961647DFFE28BAE4976FEEE136B" bold="true" box="[151,267,259,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="50">Diagnose.</emphasis>
A very small 
<taxonomicName id="4C110EF0647DFFE28A904971FDF3136B" box="[425,534,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Pericoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B965A961647DFFE28A904971FDF3136B" box="[425,534,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="50">Pericoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C110EF0647DFFE289874971FCC9136B" authorityName="Tonnoir" authorityYear="1919" box="[702,812,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Pericoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diversa">
<emphasis id="B965A961647DFFE289874971FCC9136B" box="[702,812,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="50">P. diversa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group; thorax and wings without characteristics; gonostyli markedly thinner in distal half; epandrial appendages with 5 tenacula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
